ue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### What happened?\n\nAs far as I can tell, least in a multi-binary repo, universal_binaries aren't handled well without overwriting the package names.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/aubelsb2/goreleaser-universal-binaries/runs/3889732305?check_suite_focus=true\r\n```\r\n   тип release failed after 21.67s error=failed to add: 'release-dist/goreleaser-universal-binaries_darwinall/goreleaser-universal-binaries' -> 'goreleaser-universal-binaries': file goreleaser-universal-binaries already exists in the archive\r\n```\r\nWith\r\nhttps://github.com/aubelsb2/goreleaser-universal-binaries/blob/666490c4ad458717506a34a5ed2beb0d77c26565/.goreleaser.yml\r\n\r\nI have to rename the packages:\r\n```\r\nuniversal_binaries:\r\n  - id: app1\r\n    name_template: '{{.ProjectName}}_app1_{{.Version}}'\r\n  - id: app2\r\n    name_template: '{{.ProjectName}}_app2_{{.Version}}'\r\n```\r\nAnd packages it like so:\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/20219956/137238209-da59c3e3-fd0e-439f-b70a-e6682fe7885c.png)\r\n\r\nI don't know much about universal binaries but this doesn't seem right?\n\n### How can we reproduce this?\n\nFork:\r\nhttps://github.com/aubelsb2/goreleaser-universal-binaries\r\n\r\nEnable actions and run.\n\n### goreleaser version\n\n```bash\ngoreleaser version 0.182.1\r\ncommit: d5638991c81f81b1757b24c740b58344efb2dbc0\r\nbuilt at: 2021-10-13T03:10:07Z\r\nbuilt by: goreleaser\r\nmodule version: v0.182.1, checksum: h1:cKRlHfbMxejiyMCNACsl82slFXEW+k9RggADv6/Akqg=\n```\n\n\n### GoReleaser Check\n\n- [X] goreleaser check shows no errors\n\n### Search\n\n- [X] I did search for other open and closed issues before opening this.\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [X] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_","closed_by":{"login":"caarlos0","id":245435,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI0NTQzNQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubuserco